:• '''1300''' Mbps - 3-stream 802.11ac device (80MHz wide 5GHz channel), :• '''300''' Mbps - max. PHY rate for the 40MHz wide 2.4GHz channel = '''''1600 Mbps'' class'''
{{TagLine|AC1600 Wi-Fi Dual-Band AC+ Gigabit Router}} :{{ProductPage|http://www.belkin.com/us/p/P-F9K1119/}}{{SupportPage|vendor=Belkin|pid=01t34000003qSdaAAE}} A permissive change filing with the FCC suggests that the this [[Belkin F9K1119 v2]] uses hardware identical to the [[Belkin F9K1124 v1]]. Information copied from that device. It's unclear why Belkin claims only 300 Mbps for 802.11n when this is a 3-stream device. Possibly to differentiate from the ''AC1750 DB Wi-Fi Dual-Band AC+ Gigabit Router ([[Belkin F9K1115 v2|F9K1115V2]])'' [http://www.belkin.com/us/support-article?articleNum=205537 ''Comparison between the F9K1119 v1 and v2'' from '''Belkin'''] - 2.5A appears to be wrong. Pictures of an actual F9K1119v2 on ebay show 12V/2A and confirm the FCC ID of K7SF9K1124V1.
